    <section id="roi-identification" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">ROI Identification Framework</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
        <div>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Successful workflow automation consulting relies on systematic ROI identification frameworks that quantify automation potential across different process types. These frameworks evaluate multiple factors including process volume, complexity, error rates, and strategic importance to create comprehensive ROI projections.
          </p>
          
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Process Evaluation Criteria</h3>
            <ul class="text-gray-700 space-y-3">
              <li><strong>Volume Impact:</strong> High-frequency processes offer greater automation value</li>
              <li><strong>Time Savings:</strong> Processes consuming significant human hours</li>
              <li><strong>Error Reduction:</strong> Manual processes prone to mistakes and rework</li>
              <li><strong>Compliance Benefits:</strong> Regulatory processes requiring audit trails</li>
              <li><strong>Scalability Potential:</strong> Processes that constrain business growth</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <img 
            src="https://images.pexels.com/photos/590022/pexels-photo-590022.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=800"
            alt="ROI analysis framework showing workflow automation assessment criteria and metrics"
            class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md mb-4"
          />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 italic">Comprehensive ROI analysis framework for evaluating workflow automation opportunities</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        The ROI calculation methodology incorporates both quantitative and qualitative benefits to provide comprehensive value assessment. Quantitative benefits include direct cost savings, time reduction, and error elimination. Qualitative benefits encompass improved customer satisfaction, employee engagement, and strategic agility.
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-4">ROI Calculation Formula</h3>
        <div class="text-blue-800 space-y-4">
          <p><strong>Total Benefits = Direct Savings + Indirect Benefits + Strategic Value</strong></p>
          <ul class="space-y-2">
            <li>• <strong>Direct Savings:</strong> Labor cost reduction + error cost elimination</li>
            <li>• <strong>Indirect Benefits:</strong> Improved quality + faster processing + compliance</li>
            <li>• <strong>Strategic Value:</strong> Scalability + competitive advantage + innovation enablement</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4"><strong>ROI = (Total Benefits - Implementation Cost) / Implementation Cost × 100</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        Risk assessment forms an integral part of ROI identification, considering implementation complexity, change management requirements, and technical dependencies. Processes with high ROI potential but significant implementation risks may require phased approaches or additional mitigation strategies.
      </p>
      
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Prioritization matrices help organizations focus on automation opportunities that deliver maximum value with minimal risk. These tools consider ROI potential, implementation effort, strategic alignment, and resource availability to create actionable automation roadmaps that ensure sustainable success.
      </p>
    </section>

